# Create a new documentation project

1. Open the command line interface and go to your documents folder.

2. Run the following in the command line:

    ```shell
    middleman init <project_name> -T alphagov/tech-docs-template
    ```
    where `<project_name>` is the name of your project.

3. Answer the installation questions.

4. When you see `Bundle complete!`, go to the new project folder and run `bundle install` to update the Ruby gems.

